cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.SY

This paper is primarily focused on the optimization of deep neural networks, which is a core topic in the field of machine learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses the impact of hyperparameters on the optimization process, which is relevant to the sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also includes experiments on image classification tasks, which falls under the sub-category of cs.CV (Computer Vision). The analysis of ensembling techniques is relevant to the sub-category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper discusses the large-scale structure of the loss landscape, which is relevant to the sub-category of cs.SY (Systems and Control).
